msgctxt "0000"
msgid "Yes! Lend it to me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0001"
msgid "Never mind..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0002"
msgid "I want it!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0003"
msgid "I don't need it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0004"
msgid "Riju..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0005"
msgid "Good-bye."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Near01"
msgid "<1.so>Hm hm hm..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: text_size
#. 6: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>Halt! That is the treasure of the\n"
"Gerudo, the <3.se_co>Thunder Helm<4.re_co>!<5.te_si><6.pa>\n"
"\n"
"You may be held in high esteem, but this\n"
"does not give you the freedom to lay\n"
"your hands on the pride of our people."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk01"
msgid "<1.so>Becalm yourself, Buliara.<2.pa>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: sound
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "Talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I see... And yet, despite the great debt\n"
"we owe you,<2.pa> I cannot just give such a\n"
"precious thing to you.\n"
"<3.so>...But you ARE up against the enemy of\n"
"Lady Urbosa...\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>And if you truly desire it, then perhaps\n"
"I can lend it to you...<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Well then, let's see how serious you are.\n"
"This helm is a cultural treasure. To earn\n"
"it, you must gain the trust of our people.\n"
"I want you to address their concerns and\n"
"bring a resolute peace to our town."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>This <2.se_co>Thunder Helm <3.re_co>is our cultural\n"
"treasure...\n"
"\n"
"If you want to lay hands on it, you must\n"
"show us you are serious and come back."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (longer)
#. 5: pause (longer)
#. 6: sound
#. 7: sound
#. 8: choice
msgctxt "Talk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>When I wore the <2.se_co>Thunder Helm <3.re_co>and\n"
"fought along your side, I thought I heard\n"
"a name called out on the wind.<4.pa> Riju...<5.pa>\n"
"<6.so>Heh... I hadn't been called by that name\n"
"in a while. <7.so>That strong, warm voice...\n"
"It must have belonged to Urbosa...<8.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I have heard of your recent actions.\n"
"You have returned smiles to the faces of\n"
"my people...\n"
"On behalf of all Gerudo, I must offer you\n"
"my heartfelt thanks.\n"
"\n"
"Sarqso.<2.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"You are, from this moment on, a true\n"
"friend of the Gerudo!\n"
"\n"
"And if it can help a true friend in need,\n"
"we will gladly lend you this sacred\n"
"treasure."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I know that you, more than any other,\n"
"will be able to use this <2.se_co>Thunder Helm <3.re_co>to\n"
"its fullest potential...\n"
"I believe you can unlock the power of\n"
"<4.pa>Urbosa<5.pa> that lies within."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>We already know that you are powerful.\n"
"But you can't solve all of my people's\n"
"problems with power alone."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "Talk09"
msgid "<1.so><2.te_si>Then come no closer!<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk10"
msgid "<1.so>You...desire this helm?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: pause (longer)
#. 7: sound
#. 8: choice
msgctxt "Talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You want this <2.se_co>Thunder Helm <3.re_co>that badly?\n"
"I bet you do. This special helm still holds\n"
"some of Urbosa's power.\n"
"But no matter how much we may be\n"
"indebted to you, I can't just give it away.\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>...<5.pa>And yet,<6.pa> you are setting off to carry\n"
"the fight to the enemy of Urbosa...\n"
"\n"
"<7.so>So if you truly desire it, then perhaps I\n"
"can lend it to you...<8.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>This <2.se_co>Thunder Helm<3.re_co> still holds some of\n"
"Urbosa's power.\n"
"\n"
"If you want to wield that power, then you\n"
"must address the concerns of my people\n"
"and bring a resolute peace to our town.\n"
"Then you will be acknowledged as a\n"
"friend of the Gerudo, and only then will I\n"
"lend the helm to you."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Such insolence! Even deeds as\n"
"valorous as yours do not earn you the\n"
"right to speak so to the chief!<2.pa>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk14"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm hm hm...<2.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Let it go, Buliara.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Being called by my name every once in a \n"
"while isn't so bad."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk16"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Lady Urbosa smiles upon us once more.\n"
"I must protect our fragile peace."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Within those <2.se_co>treasure chests <3.re_co>are\n"
"precious armaments once used by\n"
"Lady Urbosa herself."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>They may pale in comparison to the\n"
"<2.se_co>Thunder Helm<3.re_co>, but they are very\n"
"valuable and not easy to come by.\n"
"Since you were a friend to Lady Urbosa,\n"
"it would be best for you to have them.\n"
"\n"
"Do not hesitateâ€”take them in\n"
"your hands."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Lady Urbosa smiles upon us once more.\n"
"I must protect our fragile peace and the\n"
"<2.se_co>Thunder Helm<3.re_co> that rests here."
msgstr ""

